          "name": "Neural Machine Translation",
          "description": "",
          "date": "April 2025",
          "summary": "<ul><li><p>Developed a full-fledged English-to-Hindi audio translation pipeline integrating speech recognition, neural machine translation, and text-to-speech synthesis, aimed at improving accessibility of educational video content for non-native English speakers.</p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Implemented and evaluated two deep learning architectures for neural machine translation â€” a baseline LSTM-based Seq2Seq model and an advanced Transformer model trained on IIT Bombay and TED Talks parallel corpora. The Transformer model achieved a BLEU-1 score of 61.7\\% and BLEU-4 of 34.0\\%, producing highly accurate and fluent Hindi translations.</p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Integrated audio extraction, punctuation restoration, translation, and audio synchronization into a unified pipeline using ffmpeg, Google Speech Recognition API, Hugging Face TTS models, and custom alignment logic to produce contextually accurate, time-aligned Hindi-dubbed videos.</p></li></ul>",
          "keywords": [
            "Python",
